{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EUPpYKQE4ks4mYu99cVGLL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QaswUwoMkCvoNeYXFFHLUT","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/cockroachdb-change-plan.md << 'PLANEOF'\n# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade: Change Plan\n**Cluster:** cockroachdb namespace — crdb-cluster StatefulSet\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not execute until approved in a dedicated change window\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Version\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Binary version | v24.1.0 (build tag) |\n| Cluster version setting | 24.1 |\n| Build time | 2024-05-15 |\n| Platform | linux/amd64 |\n\n### 1.2 Topology\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| StatefulSet replicas | 3 |\n| Pod management policy | Parallel |\n| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition: 0) |\n| Nodes (all live) | crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-2 |\n| Headless service | crdb-cluster (26257/TCP, 8080/TCP) |\n| Public service | crdb-cluster-public (ClusterIP 10.96.180.137) |\n\n### 1.3 Container / Resources\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Image | cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0 |\n| CPU request/limit | 1 core |\n| Memory request/limit | 2 Gi |\n| PVC per pod (datadir) | 10 Gi (ReadWriteOnce, Retain on delete/scale) |\n| Cache | 25% of memory (--cache=25%) |\n| Max SQL memory | 25% of memory (--max-sql-memory=25%) |\n| TLS | Enabled (--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs) |\n| Secret — node cert | cockroachdb-certs |\n| Secret — client root | cockroachdb-client-root |\n\n### 1.4 Non-Default Cluster Settings\nThe following cluster settings differ from their compiled-in defaults:\n\n| Variable | Current Value | Default Value | Effect |\n|----------|--------------|---------------|--------|\n| `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled` | `false` | `true` | Automatic range merging is **disabled** |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | `208 MiB` | `32 MiB` | Rebalance/upreplication throughput capped at ~6.5x the default |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | `true` | `false` | Cluster telemetry reporting to Cockroach Labs is explicitly enabled |\n\n### 1.5 Zone Configurations\n#### System / built-in range overrides\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | Notes |\n|--------|-------------|---------------|-------|\n| `RANGE default` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | TTL reduced from CRDB compiled default (~25 h); user data baseline |\n| `DATABASE system` | 5 | 14400 | 5x replication for system database |\n| `RANGE meta` | 5 | 3600 | 5x replication for meta ranges |\n| `RANGE system` | 5 | 14400 | 5x replication for system ranges |\n| `RANGE liveness` | 5 | 600 | 5x replication, short GC for liveness |\n| `TABLE system.public.lease` | (inherited) | 600 | Short GC for lease table |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | (inherited) | 600 | |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_stats` | (inherited) | 600 | |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 | |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 | |\n| `TABLE system.public.tenant_usage` | (inherited) | 7200 | |\n| `TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | (inherited) | 3600 | |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 | |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 | |\n\n#### User data zone overrides\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |\n|--------|-------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c` | 3 | 14400 | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d` | 3 | 14400 | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target Version\n\n**Target image:** `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x` (latest stable v24.2 patch at\ntime of execution — verify at the CockroachDB releases page before the window).\n\nCockroachDB follows a `YY.R.patch` scheme. v24.1 to v24.2 is one minor release\nstep, which is the supported single-step upgrade path. Do **not** skip to v25.x\nin this window.\n\n---\n\n## 3. What Changes During the Upgrade\n\n### 3.1 Image tag (the only required change)\nThe StatefulSet image must be updated from `v24.1.0` to the new tag. Everything\nelse (resource requests, flags, volume mounts, service definitions) stays\nidentical unless explicitly noted below.\n\n```\n# Before\nimage: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\n# After\nimage: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<latest-patch>\n```\n\n### 3.2 Cluster version finalization (in-cluster, post-rollout)\nAfter all three pods are running the new binary, the operator must run:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\n```\n\nThis is a **required** step. Until it is executed, the cluster runs in a\nmixed-version compatibility mode and new v24.2 features are not available.\nThe `version` cluster setting will advance from `24.1` to `24.2`.\n\n### 3.3 Non-default cluster settings — no change required\nAll three non-default settings (`kv.range_merge.queue.enabled`,\n`kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate`, `diagnostics.reporting.enabled`) are\npreserved automatically across binary upgrades. They are stored in the\n`system.settings` table and survive pod restarts. No SQL commands are needed\nto re-apply them after the upgrade.\n\n### 3.4 Zone configurations — no change required\nZone configurations are persisted in the system catalog and are version-agnostic.\nAll zone overrides (RANGE default TTL, user table zones for\n`defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c` and `defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d`, system range\n5x-replica zones) will be intact after the upgrade without any re-application.\n\n### 3.5 TLS certificates — no change required\nThe node and client certificates in `cockroachdb-certs` and\n`cockroachdb-client-root` are not version-specific. No certificate rotation is\nneeded for this upgrade.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure (Rolling, Zero-Downtime)\n\n> All precondition checks in Step 0 must pass before proceeding.\n\n### Step 0 — Pre-upgrade validation (run before the maintenance window)\n```bash\n# Confirm all nodes are live and on v24.1\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs --all\n\n# Confirm no under-replicated ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges \\\n      WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"\n\n# Confirm cluster version is 24.1\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n```\nAll nodes must be live, under-replicated range count must be 0, version must\nreport `24.1`.\n\n### Step 1 — Update the StatefulSet image\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>\n```\nBecause `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` is set and `updateStrategy` is\n`RollingUpdate` with `partition: 0`, Kubernetes replaces pods one at a time\nstarting from the highest ordinal (crdb-cluster-2 then crdb-cluster-1 then\ncrdb-cluster-0). Each pod must pass its readiness probe before the next is\nreplaced.\n\n### Step 2 — Monitor the rollout\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n```\nWait until the rollout completes (all 3 pods running the new image and Ready).\nExpected duration: 3–8 minutes depending on image pull time\n(`imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent` skips pull if the image is already cached on\nthe node).\n\n### Step 3 — Verify all nodes are live on the new version\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs --all\n```\nAll three nodes must show the v24.2.x server version and `is_live = true`.\n\n### Step 4 — Finalize cluster version\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\"\n```\nConfirm:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n# Expected output: 24.2\n```\n\n### Step 5 — Post-upgrade smoke test\n```bash\n# No under-replicated ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges \\\n      WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"\n\n# Custom cluster settings still in place\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings \\\n      WHERE value != default_value;\"\n# Expected: kv.range_merge.queue.enabled=false, kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate=208 MiB,\n#           diagnostics.reporting.enabled=true, version=24.2\n\n# Zone configs for user tables intact\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql \\\n  --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones \\\n      WHERE target LIKE '%tenant_b%';\"\n# Expected: table_c and table_d zones with num_replicas=3, gc.ttlseconds=14400\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nCockroachDB supports downgrading the binary **before** the cluster version is\nfinalized (Step 4). If a problem is detected after the rollout (Step 2) but\nbefore version finalization:\n\n```bash\n# Roll back the image — RollingUpdate will revert pods\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n```\n\n**Once Step 4 (version finalization) is executed, downgrade is not supported.**\nAt that point, a cluster restore from a pre-upgrade backup is the only recovery\npath.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|--------|------------|\n| Image pull delay on a cold node (~400 MB image) | Low | Low | Pre-pull the image on the node before the window |\n| Under-replicated ranges during rolling restart | Low | Medium | Verify zero under-replicated ranges in Step 0; RollingUpdate only takes down one pod at a time |\n| High rebalance I/O due to `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate=208 MiB` during pod churn | Low | Medium | Monitor storage I/O during rollout; lower the setting temporarily if needed |\n| `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled=false` causes range split accumulation during upgrade | Negligible | Low | No action required; re-enable post-upgrade if desired |\n| v24.2 deprecates a zone config field or cluster setting in use | Unknown | Medium | Review the v24.2 release notes for deprecated settings before the window |\n| All pods scheduled on a single Kubernetes node (current: karma-2-control-plane) | Known | Medium | Acceptable for this single-node kind cluster environment; a production multi-node cluster should spread pods across failure domains |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Approvals Required\n\n| Role | Name | Signature | Date |\n|------|------|-----------|------|\n| DBA / Cluster Owner | | | |\n| Platform Engineering | | | |\n| Change Advisory Board | | | |\n\n---\n\n*This plan is read-only. No configuration has been applied to the live cluster.*\nPLANEOF\necho \"Written: $(wc -l < /tmp/cockroachdb-change-plan.md) lines\"","description":"Write the CockroachDB migration plan to a temp file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":221,"cache_read_input_tokens":39413,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":221},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22f49c76-84a7-4910-8dde-86050f8037fc","uuid":"d648d396-c5e9-4be8-b583-b04299c368ee","request_id":"req_011CcLc7Kju8C5F5DtcE2r8m"}
